---
import PatternLayout from '../../../../layouts/PatternLayout.astro';
---

<PatternLayout
  title="Empty States"
  description="Empty state patterns for when there's no content to display. Guide users with helpful messages and actions."
  patternName="Empty States"
  category="feedback"
  currentPath="/docs/patterns/feedback/empty-states/"
>
  <section>
    <h2>Overview</h2>
    <layout-text>
      <p>Empty states appear when a list, table, or container has no content. They should explain the situation, reassure users, and often provide an action to add content or get started.</p>
      <p><strong>Key features:</strong></p>
      <ul>
        <li>Centered layout using <code>&lt;layout-center&gt;</code></li>
        <li>Vertical grouping with <code>&lt;layout-stack&gt;</code></li>
        <li>Icons from Lucide set via <code>&lt;icon-wc&gt;</code></li>
        <li>Muted description text with <code>--color-text-muted</code></li>
        <li>Optional action buttons to guide users</li>
      </ul>
    </layout-text>
  </section>

  <section>
    <h2>Simple with Icon</h2>
    <layout-text>
      <p>A minimal empty state with an icon, heading, and description. Perfect for inline empty areas like sidebars or small panels.</p>
    </layout-text>

    <browser-window
      src="/docs/patterns/demos/empty-simple.html"
      url="https://vanilla-breeze.dev/empty-simple"
      title="Empty State - Simple"
      shadow>
    </browser-window>

    <code-block language="html" label="empty-simple.html">&lt;layout-center&gt;
  &lt;layout-stack data-gap="m" style="text-align: center; padding: var(--size-xl);"&gt;
    &lt;icon-wc name="inbox" style="--icon-size: 3rem; color: var(--color-text-muted);"&gt;&lt;/icon-wc&gt;
    &lt;h3&gt;No messages yet&lt;/h3&gt;
    &lt;p style="color: var(--color-text-muted);"&gt;
      When you receive messages, they will appear here.
    &lt;/p&gt;
  &lt;/layout-stack&gt;
&lt;/layout-center&gt;</code-block>
  </section>

  <section>
    <h2>With Illustration Placeholder</h2>
    <layout-text>
      <p>An empty state with space for a custom illustration or image. Use this for feature-level empty states where visual appeal matters.</p>
    </layout-text>

    <browser-window
      src="/docs/patterns/demos/empty-illustration.html"
      url="https://vanilla-breeze.dev/empty-illustration"
      title="Empty State - Illustration"
      shadow>
    </browser-window>

    <code-block language="html" label="empty-illustration.html">&lt;layout-center&gt;
  &lt;layout-stack data-gap="l" class="empty-state"&gt;
    &lt;!-- Illustration placeholder - replace with your own SVG or image --&gt;
    &lt;div class="illustration-placeholder"&gt;
      &lt;span class="text-sm text-muted"&gt;Illustration&lt;/span&gt;
    &lt;/div&gt;
    &lt;layout-stack data-gap="s"&gt;
      &lt;h3&gt;No projects found&lt;/h3&gt;
      &lt;p class="text-muted"&gt;
        You haven't created any projects yet. Projects help you organize your work and collaborate with your team.
      &lt;/p&gt;
    &lt;/layout-stack&gt;
  &lt;/layout-stack&gt;
&lt;/layout-center&gt;</code-block>
  </section>

  <section>
    <h2>With Action Button</h2>
    <layout-text>
      <p>An empty state with a prominent call-to-action button. Use this when users can immediately add content or take action to populate the area.</p>
    </layout-text>

    <browser-window
      src="/docs/patterns/demos/empty-action.html"
      url="https://vanilla-breeze.dev/empty-action"
      title="Empty State - With Action"
      shadow>
    </browser-window>

    <code-block language="html" label="empty-action.html">&lt;layout-card&gt;
  &lt;layout-center&gt;
    &lt;layout-stack data-gap="l" style="text-align: center; padding: var(--size-xl);"&gt;
      &lt;icon-wc name="file-text" style="--icon-size: 3rem; color: var(--color-text-muted);"&gt;&lt;/icon-wc&gt;
      &lt;layout-stack data-gap="s"&gt;
        &lt;h3&gt;No documents&lt;/h3&gt;
        &lt;p style="color: var(--color-text-muted); max-width: 36ch; margin-inline: auto;"&gt;
          Get started by creating your first document. You can upload files or start from scratch.
        &lt;/p&gt;
      &lt;/layout-stack&gt;
      &lt;button&gt;
        &lt;icon-wc name="plus"&gt;&lt;/icon-wc&gt;
        Create document
      &lt;/button&gt;
    &lt;/layout-stack&gt;
  &lt;/layout-center&gt;
&lt;/layout-card&gt;</code-block>
  </section>

  <section>
    <h2>Configuration</h2>
    <layout-text>
      <p>Empty states are composed from layout primitives. Here are the key styling considerations:</p>
    </layout-text>

    <table class="props-table">
      <thead>
        <tr>
          <th>Element</th>
          <th>Purpose</th>
          <th>Customization</th>
        </tr>
      </thead>
      <tbody>
        <tr>
          <td><code>&lt;layout-center&gt;</code></td>
          <td>Horizontally centers the content</td>
          <td>Set <code>max-width</code> via <code>data-max</code> attribute</td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
          <td><code>&lt;layout-stack&gt;</code></td>
          <td>Vertical spacing between elements</td>
          <td>Adjust gap with <code>data-gap</code> (xs, s, m, l, xl)</td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
          <td><code>&lt;icon-wc&gt;</code></td>
          <td>Visual indicator</td>
          <td>Size via <code>--icon-size</code>, color via <code>color</code></td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
          <td><code>&lt;layout-card&gt;</code></td>
          <td>Optional bordered container</td>
          <td>Use <code>data-variant</code> for different styles</td>
        </tr>
      </tbody>
    </table>
  </section>

  <section>
    <h2>Icon Options</h2>
    <layout-text>
      <p>Choose icons that represent the empty content type. Common icons from the Lucide set:</p>
      <ul>
        <li><code>inbox</code> - Messages, notifications</li>
        <li><code>file-text</code> - Documents, notes</li>
        <li><code>users</code> - People, team members</li>
        <li><code>folder</code> - Files, projects</li>
        <li><code>search</code> - Search results</li>
        <li><code>image</code> - Photos, media</li>
        <li><code>calendar</code> - Events, schedules</li>
        <li><code>shopping-cart</code> - Cart, orders</li>
      </ul>
    </layout-text>
  </section>

  <section>
    <h2>Usage Notes</h2>
    <layout-text>
      <ul>
        <li><strong>Be helpful:</strong> Explain why the area is empty and what content will appear there</li>
        <li><strong>Provide actions:</strong> When possible, include a button or link to add content</li>
        <li><strong>Keep it brief:</strong> Use short, clear messages that don't overwhelm</li>
        <li><strong>Match the context:</strong> Use icons and illustrations that relate to the content type</li>
        <li><strong>Consider states:</strong> Differentiate between "no content yet" and "no results found"</li>
      </ul>
    </layout-text>
  </section>

  <section>
    <h2>Related</h2>
    <layout-grid data-min="200px" data-gap="m">
      <a href="/docs/patterns/feedback/error-pages/" class="section-card">
        <h3>Error Pages</h3>
        <p>404, 500, and maintenance pages</p>
      </a>
      <a href="/docs/patterns/feedback/skeleton/" class="section-card">
        <h3>Skeleton</h3>
        <p>Loading placeholders for content</p>
      </a>
      <a href="/docs/elements/custom-elements/center/" class="section-card">
        <h3>Layout Center</h3>
        <p>Center content horizontally</p>
      </a>
    </layout-grid>
  </section>
</PatternLayout>
